Watching John Cassavetes film, Opening Night, I was reminded of something that Quentin Tarantino said once in an interview about personal experience in being a creator. He said:
“I don’t think there’s any such thing as this big deep insight. You get them all the time. If you don’t use what you have to say right away, then two years later it starts to just wash away and fade.”
We’ve heard this before of course about creativity in general;
